<img src="images/al_couch.png" hspace="3" vspace="5"
    width="161" height="142" align="right"
    alt="[Al, the couch potato]"/>

[A long time ago, in a mailing list far, far
away... Peter Wang said](http://alleg.sourceforge.net/docs/grozilla.en.html):
'*Given that we use "AL" so much, why have we not adopted a fat, drunk
[couch potato](http://www.bundyology.com/bal.html)
for a mascot?*'.  Later, Grzegorz Godlewski, being unable to forget this
sentence, asked Karol Krenski, who makes GPL pictures for different open source
projects, to draw the very same picture you can see to the right of this text.
Impressed? Hold your breath, because you can go to
[Karol's web page](http://www.inf.sgsp.edu.pl/pub/MALUNKI/ROZNE/)
to see this logo and many more, like the ones he drew for SDL or Postfix. He
also has the sources, so you could rescale this image or ask him to do any
modifications you may want.
<br clear="right"/>

<img src="images/logos/small_logo_by_bruno_s_drago.png" hspace="5"
   vspace="5" width="150" height="150" align="left"
   alt="[Small 150x150 logo]"/>
<a href="http://alleg.sourceforge.net/images/logos/jeff_katz/logo1.png">
<img
   src="images/logos/jeff_katz/logo1-tn.jpg" hspace="5"
   vspace="5" width="80" height="100" align="right"
   alt="[Logo by Jeff Katz]"/>
</a>
Bruno S. Drago made the small logo to the left for one of his games and
[contributed it to the Allegro community](http://sourceforge.net/mailarchive/forum.php?thread_id=3234652&forum_id=34599).
Bruno keeps working on his games, which you can find at:
<http://www.xuti.net/>.

[Jeff Katz](mailto:jeff@katzonline.net) has also contributed the logo to the
right.
You can click on it to get a higher resolution version.

<br clear="left"/><br clear="right"/>

<a href="http://alleg.sourceforge.net/images/logos/eric_pietrocupo/logo1.jpg">
<img src="images/logos/eric_pietrocupo/logo1-tn.jpg"
    hspace="5" vspace="5" width="100" height="75" align="left"
    alt="[Logo by Eric Pietrocupo]"/>
</a>
<a href="http://alleg.sourceforge.net/images/logos/andre_pereira/logo1.jpg">
<img src="images/logos/andre_pereira/logo1-tn.jpg" hspace="5"
   vspace="5" width="100" height="91" align="right"
   alt="[Logo by Andr&eacute; Luiz Pereira &Aacute;lvares]"/>
</a>
[Eric Pietrocupo](mailto:ericp@ariel.bdeb.qc.ca)
created the logo to the left
with the Windows version of [Gimp]. Click on the image
to get a bigger version.

[André Luiz Pereira Álvares](mailto:andre2k2@gmail.com)
created the logo to the right. Click on the image to get a bigger version.

<br clear="left"/>

<img src="images/logos/phoenixj_allegro.jpg" hspace="5"
   vspace="5" width="295" height="105" border=1 align="left"
   alt="[Logo by PhoenixJ]"/>
PhoenixJ made the logo to the left in Macromedia Flash. Since
the source is in vector format it can be scaled to any size (the
background color and format can consequently be changed, too). You
can visit [PhoenixJ's web page](http://www.tinsanity.net/), where you can
see more of his artwork and get his email if you want to request a
modification of this logo.

